I'm trying to add a "collapse" button to the left and right drawers in my layout
To add a "collapse" button to the left and right drawers in your layout, you can follow a general approach using HTML, CSS, and JavaScript. Below is a simple example of how you might implement this:

### HTML
Create a basic structure for your layout with two drawers and a button to collapse each drawer.

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="styles.css">
    <title>Collapsible Drawers</title>
</head>
<body>
    <div id="left-drawer" class="drawer">
        <button id="collapse-left">Collapse Left</button>
        <!-- Left drawer content -->
    </div>

    <div id="main-content">
        <!-- Main content goes here -->
    </div>

    <div id="right-drawer" class="drawer">
        <button id="collapse-right">Collapse Right</button>
        <!-- Right drawer content -->
    </div>

    <script src="script.js"></script>
</body>
</html>
```

### CSS
Define the style for your layout including the initial styles for the drawers.

```css
body {
    display: flex;
    margin: 0;
    height: 100vh;
}

.drawer {
    width: 200px;
    background-color: #f4f4f4;
    transition: width 0.3s;
}

#main-content {
    flex: 1;
    padding: 20px;
    background-color: #fff;
}

.drawer.collapsed {
    width: 0;
}
```

### JavaScript
Implement functionality to toggle the "collapsed" class on button click.

```javascript
document.getElementById('collapse-left').addEventListener('click', function() {
    document.getElementById('left-drawer').classList.toggle('collapsed');
});

document.getElementById('collapse-right').addEventListener('click', function() {
    document.getElementById('right-drawer').classList.toggle('collapsed');
});
```

### Explanation
- **HTML**: The structure includes two drawers and a main content area. Each drawer has a button that will allow it to be collapsed.
- **CSS**: The `.drawer` class is used to style the drawers, and `.collapsed` reduces the width to 0, effectively hiding it.
- **JavaScript**: Adds event listeners to the "Collapse" buttons. When clicked, they toggle the `collapsed` class on the respective drawer, triggering the transition defined in CSS.

### Adjustments
- You can customize button styles and positions as needed.
- Add animations or more complex interactions for a smoother experience.
- Consider accessibility improvements for a better user experience with screen readers.
